{
  "source_file": "Axis - Eng Procedures.docx",
  "format": "docx",
  "paragraphs": [
    {
      "index": 76,
      "text": "Appendix II",
      "style": "Heading 1",
      "bold": true,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "text": "TRANSACTION SERVICES WORKPLAN",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": true,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "text": "Unless otherwise noted, our work will concentrate on financial information for the last three fiscal years (“FY16”, “FY17”, and ”FY18”), and the latest available months in FY19.",
      "style": "Body Text",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "text": "Financial Due Diligence",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": true,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "text": "General",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": true,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "text": "Overview",
      "style": "Bullet for no #'s",
      "bold": true,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "text": "Read Target’s financial statements and discuss them with management to gain an understanding of Target’s accounting policies and practices, including:",
      "style": "Bullet for no #'s",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "text": "Finance function, financial reporting framework, and management reporting relationships;",
      "style": "Bullet for no #'s",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "text": "Significant accounting policies and estimates (e.g. revenue recognition, capitalized costs, deferred revenue) and contemplated changes",
      "style": "Bullet for no #'s",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "text": "Quality of earnings",
      "style": "Bullet for no #'s",
      "bold": true,
      "indent_level": 1,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "text": "Summarize potential adjustments identified regarding the profit and loss performance of Target in the form of a quality of earnings analysis, summarizing the risks that may impact earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation and amortization (“EBITDA”), including:",
      "style": "Bullet for no #'s",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "text": "Leveraging Target commissioned Sell-side Due Diligence Report and understand proposed adjustments (including but not limited to cash to accrual, physician compensation, pro pricing adjustments, etc);",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "text": "Large, unusual, and non-recurring events or transactions that may have distorted results;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "text": "The impact of provisions, management estimates or adjusting entries on the reported results; and",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "text": "Other potential items discovered during the due diligence process.",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "text": "Supporting analysis to Quality of Earnings",
      "style": "Bullet for no #'s",
      "bold": true,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "text": "Key performance metrics:",
      "style": "Bullet for no #'s",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 1,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "text": "By clinic analysis: Revenue and direct costs (such as doctor/compensation, rent) by location;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 2,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "text": "Revenue by type and pricing trends;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 2,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "text": "Per visit trends;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 2,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "text": "Physician production.",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 2,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "text": "Cost of revenue and corporate expenses",
      "style": "Bullet for no #'s",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 1,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "text": "Physician and employee compensation and related costs by function;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 2,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "text": "Rent;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 2,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "text": "Professional fees;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 2,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "text": "Any key supplier cost arrangements (i.e. volume rebates and minimum commitments, for top suppliers);",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 2,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "text": "Unusual and extraordinary items;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 2,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "text": "Customer acquisition expense trends (e.g. Marketing, promotion and advertising);",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 2,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "text": "Other general and administrative expenses.",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 2,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "text": "Working capital",
      "style": "Bullet for no #'s",
      "bold": true,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "text": "Obtain details on Target’s working capital and conduct the following:",
      "style": "Bullet for no #'s",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "text": "Monthly working capital trends, including seasonality, for the past 24 months;",
      "style": "Bullet with #'s",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "text": "Historical trends in key working capital metrics (DSO, DIO, DPO); and",
      "style": "Bullet with #'s",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "text": "on factors that may have distorted the current or historical working capital position.",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "text": "Supporting analysis to working capital",
      "style": "Bullet for no #'s",
      "bold": true,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "text": "Trade and other receivables",
      "style": "Bullet for no #'s",
      "bold": true,
      "indent_level": 1,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "text": "Obtain and read an analysis of the Target’s",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 1,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "text": "Inventories",
      "style": "Bullet for no #'s",
      "bold": true,
      "indent_level": 1,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "text": "Understand Target’s underlying process for recording inventory and comment on unusual items.",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 1,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "text": "Other current assets",
      "style": "Bullet for no #'s",
      "bold": true,
      "indent_level": 1,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "text": "Obtain and read an analysis of the Target’s other current assets and comment on unusual items, significant fluctuations and the existence of other balances to be potentially excluded from working capital (e.g. income taxes recoverable and deferred finance costs)",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 1,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "text": "Trade and other payables and accrued liabilities",
      "style": "Bullet for no #'s",
      "bold": true,
      "indent_level": 1,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "text": "Obtain and read an analysis of Target’s payables and accrued liabilities and inquire about:",
      "style": "Bullet for no #'s",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 1,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "text": "Terms of trade with major suppliers, aging analysis;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 2,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "text": "Accrued liabilities; and",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 2,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "text": "Other current and non-current liabilities.",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 2,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "text": "Capital expenditure requirements",
      "style": "Bullet for no #'s",
      "bold": true,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "text": "Obtain and read an analysis of existing and future capital cost requirements including:",
      "style": "Bullet for no #'s",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 1,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "text": "Maintenance versus growth capital expenditures;",
      "style": "Bullet with #'s",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "text": "Other historical, deferred, and planned capital expenditures",
      "style": "Bullet with #'s",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "text": "Net debt / debt-like items",
      "style": "Bullet for no #'s",
      "bold": true,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "text": "Summarize and comment on net debt items (on and off balance sheet) presented by management and other potential debt-like items.",
      "style": "Bullet with #'s",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "text": "Analysis of remaining liabilities surrounding contingent consideration.",
      "style": "Bullet with #'s",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "text": "Commitments and contingencies",
      "style": "Bullet for no #'s",
      "bold": true,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "text": "Inquire about significant commitments and contingent liabilities including:",
      "style": "Bullet for no #'s",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "text": "Pending or threatened litigation or investigations;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "text": "Incentive compensation;",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "text": "Purchase commitments; and",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "text": "Off-balance sheet transactions.",
      "style": "Normal",
      "bold": false,
      "indent_level": 0,
      "font_size_pt": 10.0
    }
  ],
